a a tempus in, cursus quis est. Curabitur ac lorem in mauris dictum interdum.             \n                    </p>','2018-04-30 12:43:23','2018-04-30 12:43:23'),('javautilities-strings','Strings',1,'final','tutorial','<p>\r\n	JRE provides the String class that comes with many functions. Strings are immutable objects and cannot be \r\n	changed once initialized. However, we can operate on strings by creating new string objects each time. There is no limit on \r\n	the size of the object as JVM allocates space as needed in runtime.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Strings can be initialized \r\n	using <code>new</code> keyword or using double quotes <code>\"\"</code> .\r\n</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"language-java\">String string = \"New String Object!\";</pre></code>\r\n<p>\r\n	<code>new String(\"Hello\")</code> is practically equivalent to <code>\"Hello\"</code>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Consider two strings :\r\n</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"language-java\">String string1 = \"Hello\";\r\nString string2 = \"World\";\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	All these operations are equivalent : \r\n</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"language-java\">System.out.println(string1+\" \"+string2+\"!\");</code></pre>\r\n<pre><code class=\"language-java\">System.out.println(string1.concat(\" \").concat(string2).concat(\"!\"));</code></pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	Output :\r\n</p>\r\n<pre><code class=\"language-none\">Hello World!</code></pre>\r\n<p>\r\n	However, it is preferred to use <code>StringBuffer</code> and <code>StringBuilder</code> classes to build new String as discussed later.\r\n</p>\r\n<h5>\r\n	Java String Methods\r\n</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Java String has many methods that makes operations easy. You can call these methods from any String object.\r\n	Most common methods of String are :\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>char charAt(int index)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Return character in string ar specified position.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int compareTo(String str)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int compareToIgnoreCase(String str)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String concat(String str)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns concatenated string object.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>boolean endsWith(String suffix)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns true if the caller String\'s character sequence ends with the character sequence provided.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>boolean equals(String string2)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns true if the caller String\'s character sequence is same as the character sequence provided.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>boolean equalsIgnoreCase(String string2)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns true if the caller String\'s character sequence is same as the character sequence provided, ignoring case.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int hashCode()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns a hash code for the String.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int indexOf(int character)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns index of first character found in String same as the character provided.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int indexOf(String string2)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns index of first character sequence found in string same as provided in string2.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int lastIndexOf(int character)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns index of last character found in String same as the character provided.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int lastIndexOf(String string2)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns index of last character sequence found in string same as provided in string2.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>int length()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns length of the string.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>boolean matches(String reqularExpression)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns true if the String matches the given regular expression.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String replace(Char char1, Char char2)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Replaces all instances of char1 in string with char2.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String replaceAll(String regularExpression, String value)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Replaces all sub-strings in the string matching the given regular expression with the given value.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String replaceFirst(String regularExpression, String value)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Replaces first occurrence of the regular expression in string with the given value.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String[] split(String regularExpression)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			This function splits the string value around all occurrences of the regular expression and returns as array.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String[] split(String regularExpression, int limit)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			This function splits the string value around all occurrences of the regular expression and returns as array.\r\n			The string is split up to the provided limit.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>boolean startsWith(String prefix)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns true if the string\'s character sequence starts with same as provided.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>boolean startsWith(String prefix, int offset)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns true if the string\'s character sequence starts with same as provided, at the given offset.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>CharSequence subSequence(int beginIndex, int endIndex)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns character sequence from the string starting from and ending at given index values.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String subString(int beginIndex)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns new string object with character sequence same as suffix of the string starting from given index value.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String subString(int beginIndex, int endIndex)</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns new string object with character sequence from the string starting from and ending at given index values.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>char[] toCharArray()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns character array with same character sequence of the string.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String toLowerCase()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns new string with same character sequence in lower-case letters.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String toString()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns itself.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String toUpperCase()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Returns new string with same character sequence in upper-case letters.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<h6><code>String trim()</code></h6>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Removes white spaces from beginning and end of the string and returns value.\r\n		</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>','2018-04-30 12:42:45','2018-04-30 12:42:45');
